What in the World is MedPay?

In the insurance world of North Carolina, MedPay is optional, but honestly? It shouldn't be. Its a coverage on your auto policy that pays for reasonable and necessary medical expenses for you and your passengers after an accident.

Here is the kicker: It pays out regardless of who caused the accident. Whether you hit a patch of ice on the Blue Ridge Parkway or someone rear-ends you at a stoplight in Surry CountyMedPay checks cut through the red tape.

Why Its Better Than Your Health Insurance

Most people in the Triad say, "Bill, I have health insurance! I don't need this!"

WRONG. Here is why MedPay is the ultimate sidekick:

It pays your Health Insurance Deductibles (Yes, really!).
It covers Ambulance fees (which are shockingly expensive).
It pays for Chiropractic visits to fix that whiplash.
It covers Dental repairs resulting from the crash.
NO DEDUCTIBLE on the MedPay coverage itself. First dollar coverage.

The "Pedestrian" Power-Up

Here is a fun fact to impress your friends at the next Elkin valley get-together: MedPay follows the person, not just the car.

If you are walking your dog in the neighborhood or riding your bike through the trails and you get hit by a car? Your auto MedPay kicks in. Its like having a forcefield around your wallet, even when you aren't driving.
